In [4]:
# Filter the data for Manchester United and Manchester City
teams = dfUtd[(dfUtd['Home Team'].str.contains('Man United')) | (dfUtd['Home Team'].str.contains('Man City'))]

# Extract the team names and win percentages
team_names = ['Manchester United', 'Manchester City']
win_percentages = [
    teams[teams['Home Team'] == 'Man United']['Win Percentage'].mean(),  # Average win percentage for Man United
    teams[teams['Home Team'] == 'Man City']['Win Percentage'].mean()  # Average win percentage for Man City
]

# Create the bar chart
bars = plt.bar(team_names, win_percentages, color=['red', 'lightblue'], label=['Manchester United', 'Manchester City'])

# Adding labels and title
plt.xlabel('Teams')
plt.ylabel('Win Percentage')
plt.title('Win Percentage Man United vs Man City, ETH first 3 seasons Versus Guardiola')

# Display the precise win percentage above the bars
for bar in bars:
    yval = bar.get_height()
    plt.text(bar.get_x() + bar.get_width()/2, yval, f'{yval:.2f}%', ha='center', va='bottom')

# Display the bar chart
plt.show()

# Filter Premier League games for Manchester United from dfUtd
dfUnited = dfUtd[(dfUtd['Competition'] == 'Premier League') &
                 ((dfUtd['Home Team'] == 'Man United') | (dfUtd['Away Team'] == 'Man United'))]

# Filter Premier League games for Manchester City from dfUtd
dfCity = dfUtd[(dfUtd['Competition'] == 'Premier League') &
               ((dfUtd['Home Team'] == 'Man City') | (dfUtd['Away Team'] == 'Man City'))]

# Count Wins for Manchester United and Manchester City
united_wins = len(dfUnited[dfUnited['Result'] == 'W'])
city_wins = len(dfCity[dfCity['Result'] == 'W'])

# Count total games played by Manchester United and Manchester City in the Premier League
united_games_played = len(dfUnited)
city_games_played = len(dfCity)

# Calculate win percentages
united_win_percentage = (united_wins / united_games_played) * 100 if united_games_played > 0 else 0
city_win_percentage = (city_wins / city_games_played) * 100 if city_games_played > 0 else 0

# Print win percentages
print(f"Manchester United Win Percentage in Premier League: {united_win_percentage:.2f}%")
print(f"Manchester City Win Percentage in Premier League: {city_win_percentage:.2f}%")

Manchester United Win Percentage in Premier League: 52.87%

# Calculate total count of goals and average goals per game for Manchester United
total_goals = 0

def calculate_goals(row):
    try:
        if row['Home Team'] == 'Man United':
            return int(row['Home Score'].split()[0])
        elif row['Away Team'] == 'Man United':
            return int(row['Away Score'].split()[0])
    except ValueError:
        return 0
    return 0

# Apply function to calculate goals scored by Manchester United
dfUtd['United Goals'] = dfUtd.apply(calculate_goals, axis=1)

total_goals = dfUtd['United Goals'].sum()
number_of_games = len(dfUtd[(dfUtd['Home Team'] == 'Man United') | (dfUtd['Away Team'] == 'Man United')])
average_goals_per_game = total_goals / number_of_games if number_of_games > 0 else 0

# Print total count of goals and average goals per game
print(f"Total goals scored by Manchester United: {total_goals}")
print(f"Average goals per game scored by Manchester United: {average_goals_per_game:.2f}")

Total goals scored by Manchester United: 229
Average goals per game scored by Manchester United: 1.57

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Calculate average goals per game for Manchester United and Manchester City
number_of_games_united = len(dfUtd[(dfUtd['Home Team'] == 'Man United') | (dfUtd['Away Team'] == 'Man United')])
number_of_games_city = len(dfUtd[(dfUtd['Home Team'] == 'Man City') | (dfUtd['Away Team'] == 'Man City')])

total_goals_united = dfUtd['United Goals'].sum()
total_goals_city = dfUtd['City Goals'].sum()

average_goals_per_game_united = total_goals_united / number_of_games_united if number_of_games_united > 0 else 0
average_goals_per_game_city = total_goals_city / number_of_games_city if number_of_games_city > 0 else 0

# Create a bar chart to compare average goals per game between Manchester United and Manchester City
teams = ['Manchester United', 'Manchester City']
average_goals = [average_goals_per_game_united, average_goals_per_game_city]

plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
bars = plt.bar(teams, average_goals, color=['red', 'blue'])

# Add the average goals per game above each bar
for bar in bars:
    yval = bar.get_height()
    plt.text(bar.get_x() + bar.get_width()/2, yval + 0.05, f'{yval:.2f}', ha='center', va='bottom')

# Add titles and labels
plt.title('Average Goals Per Game Comparison: Manchester United vs Manchester City')
plt.xlabel('Team')
plt.ylabel('Average Goals Per Game')

# Display the chart
plt.show()

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Calculate total goals conceded for Manchester United and Manchester City
def calculate_goals_conceded_united(row):
    try:
        if row['Home Team'] == 'Man United':
            return int(row['Away Score'].split()[0])
        elif row['Away Team'] == 'Man United':
            return int(row['Home Score'].split()[0])
    except ValueError:
        return 0
    return 0

def calculate_goals_conceded_city(row):
    try:
        if row['Home Team'] == 'Man City':
            return int(row['Away Score'].split()[0])
        elif row['Away Team'] == 'Man City':
            return int(row['Home Score'].split()[0])
    except ValueError:
        return 0
    return 0

dfUtd['United Goals Conceded'] = dfUtd.apply(calculate_goals_conceded_united, axis=1)
dfUtd['City Goals Conceded'] = dfUtd.apply(calculate_goals_conceded_city, axis=1)

total_goals_conceded_united = dfUtd['United Goals Conceded'].sum()
total_goals_conceded_city = dfUtd['City Goals Conceded'].sum()

number_of_games_united = len(dfUtd[(dfUtd['Home Team'] == 'Man United') | (dfUtd['Away Team'] == 'Man United')])
number_of_games_city = len(dfUtd[(dfUtd['Home Team'] == 'Man City') | (dfUtd['Away Team'] == 'Man City')])

average_goals_conceded_per_game_united = total_goals_conceded_united / number_of_games_united if number_of_games_united > 0 else 0
average_goals_conceded_per_game_city = total_goals_conceded_city / number_of_games_city if number_of_games_city > 0 else 0

# Create a bar chart to compare average goals conceded per game between Manchester United and Manchester City
teams = ['Manchester United', 'Manchester City']
average_goals_conceded = [average_goals_conceded_per_game_united, average_goals_conceded_per_game_city]

plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
bars = plt.bar(teams, average_goals_conceded, color=['red', 'blue'])

# Add the average goals conceded per game above each bar
for bar in bars:
    yval = bar.get_height()
    plt.text(bar.get_x() + bar.get_width()/2, yval + 0.05, f'{yval:.2f}', ha='center', va='bottom')

# Add titles and labels

# Calculate total goals scored and conceded by Manchester United against top 5 teams
def parse_score(score):
    try:
        return int(score.split()[0])
    except ValueError:
        return 0

# Apply score parsing to Manchester United
total_goals_united_scored = dfUnited_top5.apply(lambda row: parse_score(row['Home Score']) if row['Home Team'] == 'Man United' else parse_score(row['Away Score']), axis=1).sum()
total_goals_united_conceded = dfUnited_top5.apply(lambda row: parse_score(row['Away Score']) if row['Home Team'] == 'Man United' else parse_score(row['Home Score']), axis=1).sum()

# Calculate total goals scored and conceded by Manchester City against top 5 teams
total_goals_city_scored = dfCity_top5.apply(lambda row: parse_score(row['Home Score']) if row['Home Team'] == 'Man City' else parse_score(row['Away Score']), axis=1).sum()
total_goals_city_conceded = dfCity_top5.apply(lambda row: parse_score(row['Away Score']) if row['Home Team'] == 'Man City' else parse_score(row['Home Score']), axis=1).sum()

# Print total goals scored and conceded
print(f"Total goals scored by Manchester United against top 5 teams: {total_goals_united_scored}")
print(f"Total goals conceded by Manchester United against top 5 teams: {total_goals_united_conceded}")

print(f"Total goals conceded by Manchester City against top 5 teams: {total_goals_city_conceded}")

# Filter for Manchester United games in the Premier League against rest of the league
dfUnited_rest = dfUtd[(dfUtd['Competition'] == 'Premier League') &
                      ((dfUtd['Home Team'] == 'Man United') & (~dfUtd['Away Team'].isin(top_5_teams))) |
                      ((dfUtd['Away Team'] == 'Man United') & (~dfUtd['Home Team'].isin(top_5_teams)))]

# Filter for Manchester City games in the Premier League against rest of the league
dfCity_rest = dfUtd[(dfUtd['Competition'] == 'Premier League') &
                    ((dfUtd['Home Team'] == 'Man City') & (~dfUtd['Away Team'].isin(top_5_teams))) |
                    ((dfUtd['Away Team'] == 'Man City') & (~dfUtd['Home Team'].isin(top_5_teams)))]

num_games_city_rest = len(dfCity_rest)

total_goals_city_conceded_rest = dfCity_rest.apply(lambda row: parse_score(row['Away Score']) if row['Home Team'] == 'Man City' else parse_score(row['Home Score']), axis=1).sum()
